<br>
At 59:<br>
* IM (instrument mastery) - fantastic... great for soloing, and raiding<br>
* SM (singing mastery) - not bad... imo pretty much only useful for raid group only resists (PoV), not much else of use uses the singing skill<br>
* JF (jam fest) - complete waste of time... currently it is broken so it doesnt benifit group members, it also caps out your skill at level 65, so once you are 63 you would refund your aa points as it does nothing at all for you.<br>
* PE (physical enhancement) - very good...ups your ND, CA, CS skills by a couple of percent<br>
* EN (extended notes) - ok.... good for your aoe spells, it widens the range of them, personally way way down on my list of things to get.<br>
<br>
At 55 (why did i do these back to front):<br>
* MC (mental clarity) - not bad.... definatly get MC1, however i wouldnt go higher as swarm kiting you can maintain mana constantly with 4 mana regen. Either go for MC3 or get yourself a few FT items (lots of cheap ones around, solstice, owlbear eye etc etc)<br>
* ND (natural durability) - very good.... more hp = safer bard. helps soloing, grouping, pulling, raiding<br>
* CA (combat avoidance) - good.... makes you get by melee hit less often, thus avoiding damage and avoiding stunning kicks etc. Useful grouping and soloing.<br>
* CS (combat stability) - ok... makes you get hit for less, thus avoiding damage. Not bad, but CA is better in every aspect because as a bard we are better off not being hit rather than being hit for less (the stuns interupt our songs too much).<br>
<br>
So in summary for your 12 aa worth of 55 thingies I would suggest for you..<br>
MC1<br>
ND2<br>
CA1<br>
CS1<br>
<br>
or something like that (the reason for a touch of CS and CA is so they get affected by PE at 59)<br>
<br>
ps. keep in mind that MC1 costs 2aa, then MC2 costs you another 4aa and MC3 costs you another 6aa... getting MC3 thus costs you all 12 of your 55 aa.<br>
<br>
(edit: added the ps)<br>
