<br>
IM gives a massive boost to pretty much all of your songs, especially your big aoe dragon resist songs. With IM3 you add another 0.6 mod to the song, pretty much the difference between using a combine drum and tdok. This difference also applies to your aoe regen spell, your damage shield spells (except PoV) and pretty much everything else that is useful.<br>
<br>
IM is good for soloing, grouping and raiding, whilst EN is only good for raiding (maybe some group situations).<br>
<br>
But then again maybe thats me, I am in a larger guild that can afford to have more than 1 bard on a raid so we can spread it out a bit... then again our casters all know how to duck in and out of aoe's so we dont really need to give them resists either.... (and half the pop fights the aoe's are unresistable so we pretty much dont bother).<br>
<br>
Also as a bard we can make fairly reasonable xp group tanks with CA and LR, over the last few days I have been tanking all sorts of mobs in HoH, BoT and the mini's in SolC. With CA maxed and our 50% slow we do a pretty reasonable job of it, only your group has to be pretty damn good at managing their agro because if a mob peels off onto the chanter its going to take us AGES to get it back again (anyone know any bard techniques to build agro quickly??).<br>
<br>
Oh yeah and Bella is right, absolutly no focus items work for bards... I would give my left hand to for to be able to use extended range focus items...<br>
